context: The city provides sewage disposal and water supply services, with water coming from the <b1_0>Huron River<b1_0/> and groundwater sources. These facilities serve the city, which is divided into five water districts. The city's water department also operates four dams along the Huron River, two of which provide hydroelectric power. The city also offers waste management services, with <b3_0>Recycle Ann Arbor<b3_0/> handling recycling service. Other utilities are provided by private entities. Electrical power and gas are provided by DTE Energy. <b4_0>AT&T Inc.<b4_0/> is the primary wired telephone service provider for the area.
